  <brief_title>Vasoactive Hormones During the Night in Patients With Obstructive Sleep Apnea Before and After Treatment With CPAP.</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Regional Hospital Holstebro</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Regional Hospital Holstebro</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      We wanted to test the hypothesis that treatment with continuous positive airway pressure
      reduces nocturnal hypoxia and thereby affecting levels of vasoactive hormones leading to a
      fall in blood pressure patients with obstructive sleep apnea.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
